MCI owns and administers the computers (I assume), so the computers
should be named within the MCI.COM domain.  If I send a message from a
Berkeley computer, that computer shouldn't be renamed just because I'm
a Stanford student.  Are there examples where the ownership or 
administration test breaks down?

Peter

